<ul>
  <li>Teams have <strong>30 minutes</strong> for each problem, and they can stop the time if they think they have worked out the problem. However, if after stopping the time the solution turns out to be wrong, the team will lose 10 points.</li>
</ul>

<p><span class="capsule"><strong>Result-like problem.</strong></span> Compute the product
\[\left(1-\frac41\right)\left(1-\frac49\right)
\left(1-\frac4{25}\right)\cdots\]</p>

<p><span class="capsule"><strong>Proof-like problem.</strong></span> Show that
\[\cos\left(\frac{\pi}5\ \right)=\frac{1+\sqrt{5}}4.\]</p>

<p><span class="capsule"><strong>Mixed problem.</strong></span> Show that the sequence defined by $a_1:=1$,
\[a_n:=\sqrt{1+a_{n-1}},\qquad n&gt;1\]
is convergent, and find its limit.</p>

<ul>
  <li>In a mixed problem, the 10 points <strong>split</strong> in two: 5 points for the result-like part, and 5 points for the proof-like part.</li>
  <li>No calculator allowed.</li>
</ul>
